Boost:
1. wget https://dl.bintray.com/boostorg/release/1.65.0/source/boost_1_65_0.tar.gz
1. tar zxvf boost_1_65_0.tar.gz
2. cd boost_1_65_0
3. bootstrap.sh
4. ./b2 --with-filesystem --with-system --with-program_options --with-thread --with-regex --with-chrono --with-iostreams --prefix=<destination path> toolset=gcc variant=release link=static threading=multi runtime-link=static


Xcerces
1. wget http://ftp.wayne.edu/apache//xerces/c/3/sources/xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz
2. tar zxvf xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz
3. cd xerces-c-3.2.0
4. ./configure CFLAGS=-O3 CXXFLAGS=-O3 --prefix=<destination path> --enable-transcoder-iconv --disable-network
5. cd src; make install

Xalan
1. wget http://apache.cs.utah.edu/xalan/xalan-c/sources/xalan_c-1.11-src.tar.gz
2. tar zxvf xalan_c-1.11-src.tar.gz
3. export XERCESCROOT=<path>/xerces-c-3.2.0/
4. export XALANCROOT=<path>/xalan-c-1.11/c/
5. ./runConfigure -p linux -c gcc -x g++ -b 64
6. edit src/xalanc/Makefile 
7. edit src/xalanc/Utils/XalanMsgLib/Makefile. 
8. see the Makefile and patch in the directory
9. make

Proteomics Wizards
1. download pwiz
2. cp library/boost_aux/ to src/pwiz/boost 
3. use makefile in this folder

Download links:
1. boost 1.65.0 (boost_1_65_0.tar.gz): https://dl.bintray.com/boostorg/release/1.65.0/source/boost_1_65_0.tar.gz
2. xerces-c-3.2.0 (xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz): http://ftp.wayne.edu/apache//xerces/c/3/sources/xerces-c-3.2.0.tar.gz
3. xalan 1.11 (xalan_c-1.11-src.zip): http://apache.cs.utah.edu/xalan/xalan-c/sources/xalan_c-1.11-src.tar.gz
4. pwiz: http://proteowizard.sourceforge.net/downloads.shtml
